snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Moriah,
I customize dolls. Doll customizers use Mister Super Clear UV cut spray to prep plastic surfaces for painting. It creates a barrier between the plastic and the paint. You need to use a mask when applying it because breathing it in is BAD! Read all the warnings carefully.

Another thing you can try is Liquitex Matte varnish to prep your surfaces

For a final top coat... im really not sure what you can use to make it dishwasher safe or super scratch proof. Mister Super Clear does a good job of sealing paint in. But since I've used it primarily for dolls (which don't go in the dishwasher!) I can't really say how well it will work. I've tried washing my work off with soap and water and it held fairly well. But I would definitely test on something else first.

There are so called permanent craft paints on the market but I've never tested them.

If you find something that works, please share cuz I have a bunch of stuff I'd use it on! Good luck!
